properties.Title: Update: Flood Warning Issued For The Churchill River From The Saskatchewan-Manitoba Border To Leaf Rapids Manitoba
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructureâ€™s Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a Flood Warning for the Churchill River from the Saskatchewan-Manitoba Border to Leaf Rapids Manitoba. If you are in the affected area, be watchful as local waterways are expected to rise quickly and may cause flooding. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Use caution when driving on all roads as road conditions may have changed. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by local authorities and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Stay tuned to local media for updates. Up to date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca
Expires: 2020-07-20T16:00:00-05:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization, 2020-07-13T15:49:20-05:00, 23685E07-AFF8-0A95-CDD1-15866C030FE7
Area: Churchill River from the Saskatchewan-Manitoba Border to Leaf Rapids Manitoba
properties.Author: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization

properties.Title: Update: Dam Overflow Alert Issued By Manitoba Infrastructure In The Areas Of Riverdale Municipality And Rm Of Whitehead
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure is advising that risk of dam failure at the RIVERS RESERVOIR DAM continues at lower risk. Inspection results and lower water levels and flow have lowered the risk of imminent failure and evacuation orders for the inundation area can be lifted. Failure of the dam would result in extreme flooding and dangerous situations. Residents in the inundation zones should remain ready to evacuate on short notice if conditions change. Avoid water bodies, valleys, low lying areas and affected areas. Move to higher ground if required and avoid flooded areas. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca.
Expires: 2020-07-17T16:00:00-05:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization, 2020-07-13T15:58:02-05:00, A91F37A4-F2D3-8DE7-E6E5-9EF3EB00BBA9
Area: Little Saskatchewan River in the Riverdale Municipality and RM of Whitehead.

This severe thunderstorm is currently located between Esterhazy and Yarbo and is tracking to the east at 30 km/h. Quarter sized hail was recently reported near Esterhazy with this severe thunderstorm. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles. Remember, severe thunderstorms can produce tornadoes. Severe thunderstorm warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.
Expires: 2020-07-13T23:23:31-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2020-07-13T20:25:31-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.4231273897.2020

properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Rain, at times heavy, continues. A narrow band of heavy rain will bring significant rainfall to some locations today and tomorrow. General rainfall amounts are expected to be in the 40 to 60 mm range with local amounts up to 100 mm possible by the time the heaviest rain eases Tuesday afternoon. Showery conditions with local amounts can be expected through mid week. ### Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. Rainfall warnings are issued when significant rainfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NTStorm.
Expires: 2020-07-14T08:18:04-00:00
